bwstring.value: An event staged to raise money for a unit or organization.
Any graduation event staged by a University unit or the University as a whole.
All forms of dance, including dance performance and dances
Events sponsored by health sciences units.
A larger gathering (more than 50 people) that could be on an academic subject or a more general one, in which most of the communication is from speaker to audience.
An event in which a unit or organization invites visitors to their location during specified hours.

A relatively small gathering (less than 50 people), usually on an academic subject, in which the speaker expects a lot of interaction. For purposes of this calendar, colloquia and symposia are considered seminars.
An event that does not occur on a regular basis and doesn't fit any other category
Competitive events in football, basketball, baseball, etc.
When a unit offers to guide visitors through their facilities at a specified time.
A single session or ongoing class sponsored by a unit.
A series of meetings around a particular theme that lasts from half a day up to several days.
A meeting that usually involves several speakers on a particular topic and a fair amount of interaction with the audience.
A one-session class on a particular topic.
A single session of a particular group or organization that lasts less than half a day.
USE ONLY IF NO OTHER CATEGORY EXISTS, and please contact us
Social gatherings too broad to fit into other categories
